After much anticipation, Every Nite, the new EP from celebrated Canadian trio Keys N Krates is finally here! Out today on Dim Mak Records, Every Nite has already received a huge amount of recognition from other artists and from the media. A follow up to 2013’s SOLOW EP, Every Nite displays the seamless blend and complementary juxtaposition between the drums, keys, turntables, and live sampling that so clearly distinguishes the three-piece live electronic band. attachments.title: Premiere: DJ Marky 'Silly' by Mixmag
attachments.text:
<http://www.mixmag.net/read/dj-marky-silly-premieres>

Yes. It's the return of DJ Marky. The Brazilian magician's been in the studio, wrapped up his debut solo artist album and is set to release it just in time for those summer BBQs, parties in the park and rooftop raves. 

Although he's no stranger to an LP - don't forget he hooked up with fellow Brazilian XRS for 2004 gem 'In Rotation' - this is the first time he'll be releasing his own, with his label Innerground Records its home. What can we expect? That unmistakable drum 'n' bass funk of his and a couple of disco-dashed numbers.
